        "timestamp": 1777411997
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13224#discussion_r3157343450\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also: we have some holes with CM async, right? Should that be noted here?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 591581339,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1777411997
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> cfallin created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13224#discussion_r3157341904\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Rather than <code>etc</code> here and above, could we spell out what we mean a bit more? It feels like a little bit too much ambiguity (especially with specific functions listed above it), and one could reasonably interpret \"yes\" to \"etc\" to mean \"all of the runtime\" (aka \"all of Wasmtime aside from the compiler\" to some observers)</p>\n<p>Perhaps: \"remaining APIs for instantiation and execution of Wasm\"?</p>\n</blockquote>",
